    "body": "Based on #14 \r\n\r\nWe might want to define a json schema for this (largely based on https://github.com/PrismarineJS/minecraft-data/blob/master/schemas/protocol_schema.json ) and expose the schema checking function. (and maybe even expose the schema, so it could be used as a subschema in minecraft-data)",
    "closed_at": "2015-12-01T11:31:40Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "body": "I'd like to avoid schemas. They have proved to not be flexible enough for checking. Instead, adding a verification function to the dataTypes and a script to statically check that a protodef file passes the verifications seems like a much better idea. ",
